# History

### 0.3 (2021-03-11)
 - Add '?' as synonym for 'help' in interactive mode.
 - Quit interactive mode when end-of-file (CTRL-D) is encountered.
 - Remove '-rN' option.
 - Rename '-h' option to '-?'.
 - Rename '-v' option to '-#'.
 - Remove '--loud' option. Rename '-l' option to '-v', shorthand for
   '--verbose'.
 - Rewrite the help message and error messages to be more descriptive.

### 0.2 (2017-04-16)
 - Add '-rN' and '--rolls=N', for specifying how many times to roll the dice
   before exiting.
 - Remove '-1' and '--once'.
 - Add '-q'/'--quiet' and '-l'/'--loud'/'--verbose', for specifying how user-
   friendly the output should be. (useful for shell piping)
 - Output prompt '>>> ' in interactive mode.
 - Replace scons with make.

### 0.1 (2016-07-22)
 - Pad spaces before dice rolls so that output is always aligned in columns.
